<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Detroit Piston John Salley debuts this weekend
with the Detroit Symphony Orchestra _ narrating ``Casey at the
Bat.'' And he says that's as close to baseball as he wants to come.
   ``I don't like the idea of this white thing coming at your head
90 miles an hour,'' said Salley, a forward on the two-time National
Basketball Association champion team.
   Salley said he was happy to do the show, though.
   ``I got time, plus it's cultural. I like all music except heavy
metal,'' he said.
   And his ultimate goal in music?
   ``I just one day want to be able to go to a club, see a piano
and entertain everybody,'' he said. ``I can't say I can sing, but I
can talk a lot of words.''
</TEXT>
